The paper proposes a method for classification of incomplete patterns using adaptive imputation of missing values based on belief function theory. This involves using techniques such as K-nearest neighbor and Self-Organizing Map for imputation, and an ensemble classifier for credal classification. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), neural networks (cs.NE), and computational intelligence (cs.SI), making these sub-categories the most likely for this paper.
